
@startuml

' Define classes
class Employee {
  - name: String
  - socialSecurityNumber: String
}

abstract class CreativeEmployee {
  - hasOscar: Boolean
}

class Director extends CreativeEmployee {
  - assistantName: String
}

class Actor extends CreativeEmployee {
  - education: String
}

class Technician extends Employee {
  - fieldOfActivity: String
}

class FilmSet {
  - location: String
}

class Film {
  - title: String
  - yearOfRelease: Integer
  - genre: Genre (enum)
}

enum Genre {
  Thriller
  Action
  Horror
  Comedy
}

class Screenwriter {
  - name: String
  - mostSuccessfulFilm: String
}

class Screenplay {
  - title: String
  - version: Integer
  - date: Date
  - numberOfScenes: Integer
  - plot: String
  - sourceType: SourceType (enum)
}

enum SourceType {
  Novel
  Concept
}

class Novel {
  - title: String
  - author: String
}

' Relationships
Employee <|-- CreativeEmployee
CreativeEmployee <|-- Director
CreativeEmployee <|-- Actor
Employee <|-- Technician

FilmSet "0..*" -- "1" Film : used in
Film "0..*" -- "1" FilmSet : shot at

Screenwriter "1" -- "0..*" Screenplay : writes
Screenplay "1" -- "1" Film : written for
Screenplay "0..1" -- "1" Novel : based on

Film "1" -- "0..*" Actor : features
Film "1" -- "1" Director : directed by
Film "1" -- "1" Screenplay : based on
Film "1" -- "0..*" Technician : uses

Actor "1" -- "1" Screenplay : reads

@enduml

---

### Explanation of Key Elements:

- **Employee** is the base class with all staff members.
- **CreativeEmployee** is an abstract class extended by **Director** and **Actor**, both of which can have an Oscar.
- **Technician** is another type of employee with a specific activity field.
- **FilmSet** has a one-to-many relationship with **Film**.
- **Film** belongs to a **Genre** (enumerated).
- **Screenwriter** writes multiple **Screenplays**, each for exactly one **Film**.
- **Screenplay** may be based on a **Novel** or a **Concept**.
- **Actors** read the screenplay for the film they are acting in.
- **Directors** implement the screenplay.

